{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877760874,"sessionID":"ses_285712c33ffeKLPVuYWhDtZwf2","part":{"id":"prt_d7a90274f001DcMmBanuLEoH2h","messageID":"msg_d7a8ee3f60015AAUDfF046ezaf","sessionID":"ses_285712c33ffeKLPVuYWhDtZwf2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-668faed03f51492b901a3001bbb9b1cd","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a dual-provider deployment system for the AgentCube CLI that enables AI agents to be deployed to either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR). This feature provides users with flexibility in deployment targets while maintaining a consistent CLI experience.\n\n## Motivation\n\nUsers have different infrastructure setups:\n- **Standard Kubernetes**: Teams with existing K8s clusters who want to deploy agents as standard Deployments and NodePort Services\n- **AgentCube CRD**: Teams using the AgentCube operator (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh) who benefit from specialized CRD features like session management, workload manager integration, and router-based invocation\n\nSupporting both deployment targets from a single CLI tool reduces operational complexity and enables gradual adoption of AgentCube-specific features.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class for AgentRuntime CRD |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Provider selection logic in `publish` command |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Provider-aware invocation routing |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Provider-specific status retrieval |\n| CLI commands | `--provider` flag for `publish`, `invoke`, `status` commands |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Cloud build mode implementation (future AR)\n- Helm chart generation\n- Multi-cluster deployment\n- GitOps integration\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      CLI (main.py)                          │\n│  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Runtime Layer                             │\n│  PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │ StatusRuntime            │\n│         │              │               │                    │\n│         └──────────────┴───────────────┘                    │\n│                        │                                    │\n│                        ▼                                    │\n│              provider: \"agentcube\" | \"k8s\"                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n          ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐\n          ▼                           ▼\n┌───────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────┐\n│ KubernetesProvider│     │ AgentCubeProvider │\n│                   │     │                   │\n│ • Deployment      │     │ • AgentRuntime CR │\n│ • NodePort Service│     │ • CRD v1alpha1    │\n│ • wait_for_ready  │     │ • session mgmt    │\n└───────────────────┘     └───────────────────┘\n          │                           │\n          └───────────┬───────────────┘\n                      ▼\n            Kubernetes API Server\n                      │\n          ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n          ▼                       ▼\n   ┌─────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐\n   │ Deployment  │      │ AgentRuntime CR │\n   │ + Service   │      │ (Operator)      │\n   └─────────────┘      └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. KubernetesProvider (`k8s_provider.py`)\n\nStandard Kubernetes deployment using `kubernetes` Python client:\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)\n    def deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint, replicas, node_port, env_vars) -> Dict\n    def get_agent_status(agent_name) -> Dict\n    def delete_agent(agent_name) -> Dict\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120) -> None\n```\n\n**Deployment Strategy:**\n- Creates `apps/v1` Deployment with configurable replicas\n- Creates `v1` Service of type NodePort (range 30000-32767)\n- Uses `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` for local development\n- Names sanitized to DNS-compliant format (lowercase, hyphens only)\n\n### 2. AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube_provider.py`)\n\nCustom Resource deployment for AgentCube operator:\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint, env_vars, workload_manager_url, router_url, readiness_probe_path, readiness_probe_port) -> Dict\n    def get_agent_runtime(name, namespace) -> Optional[Dict]\n```\n\n**CRD API:**\n- Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- Version: `v1alpha1`\n- Plural: `agentruntimes`\n\n**CR Spec Fields:**\n| Field | Source |\n|-------|--------|\n| `image` | `image_url` |\n| `entrypoint` | `entrypoint` |\n| `port` | `port` |\n| `env` | `env_vars` + WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL + ROUTER_URL |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `\"15m\"` |\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `\"8h\"` |\n| `readinessProbe` | From metadata or defaults |\n| `imagePullSecrets` | `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]` |\n\n### 3. Provider Selection Logic\n\n**Publish Command (`--provider` flag):**\n\n| Provider | Behavior |\n|----------|----------|\n| `k8s` | `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` → `wait_for_deployment_ready()` |\n| `agentcube` | `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` |\n\n**Status Command:**\n\n| Provider | Status Source |\n|----------|---------------|\n| `k8s` | Deployment status + Service NodePort |\n| `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR `.status` field |\n\n**Invoke Command:**\n\n| Provider | Endpoint Pattern |\n|----------|------------------|\n| `k8s` | `http://localhost:{node_port}` (direct) |\n| `agentcube` | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` |\n\n### 4. Metadata Extensions\n\nNew fields in `AgentMetadata`:\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | URL for Workload Manager (AgentCube CR) |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | URL for Router (AgentCube CR) |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | Health check path |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | Health check port |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | Agent ID from AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session ID for invocation |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict]` | Deployment metadata |\n\n### 5. CLI Command Updates\n\n**`publish` command:**\n```python\n--provider: str = \"agentcube\"  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n--node-port: Optional[int] = None  # For k8s provider (30000-32767)\n--replicas: Optional[int] = None   # For k8s provider\n--namespace: Optional[str] = None\n```\n\n**`invoke` command:**\n```python\n--provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n--header: Optional[List[str]] = None  # Repeatable\n```\n\n**`status` command:**\n```python\n--provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional dep in `k8s` extra) |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata validation |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invoke |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error | Provider | Message |\n|-------|----------|---------|\n| Missing router_url/workload_manager_url | agentcube | \"Both router_url and workload_manager_url required in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n| Deployment timeout | k8s | `TimeoutError` after 120s |\n| Invalid node_port | k8s | Must be 30000-32767 |\n| CRD not found | agentcube | Check AgentCube operator installation |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Mock `kubernetes.client` for `KubernetesProvider`\n- Mock dynamic client for `AgentCubeProvider`\n- Test provider selection in `PublishRuntime`\n- Test endpoint routing in `InvokeRuntime`\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Minikube/KIND cluster for k8s provider\n- Mocked AgentCube operator for agentcube provider\n- End-to-end: pack → build → publish → invoke → status\n\n## Migration Path\n\nExisting users (provider not specified):\n1. `publish` defaults to `agentcube` provider\n2. Metadata fields `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` must be configured\n3. Users wanting standard K8s should set `--provider k8s`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider agentcube` creates AgentRuntime CR\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s` routes to NodePort endpoint\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider agentcube` routes through Router\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s` shows Deployment pod status\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --provider agentcube` shows CR status\n- [ ] NodePort range validation (30000-32767)\n- [ ] Missing agentcube config raises clear error\n- [ ] Namespace isolation works for both providers\n- [ ] All commands support `--verbose` for detailed logging\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| K8s client dependency size | Make `kubernetes` an optional extra (`pip install agentcube[k8s]`) |\n| CRD API drift | Pin to `v1alpha1` and document compatibility |\n| Deployment timeout on slow clusters | Configurable timeout (default 120s) |\n| Multiple kubeconfig contexts | Support `--kubeconfig` flag (future) |\n\n## Timeline\n\n| Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n|-------|----------|--------------|\n| Phase 1 | 2 days | `KubernetesProvider` implementation |\n| Phase 2 | 2 days | `AgentCubeProvider` implementation |\n| Phase 3 | 1 day | Provider selection in runtime classes |\n| Phase 4 | 1 day | CLI command updates and metadata fields |\n| Phase 5 | 2 days | Testing (unit + integration) |\n| Phase 6 | 1 day | Documentation and examples |\n\n**Total: ~9 days**\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` — CLI package structure\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Command specifications\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — AgentRuntime CRD client (Go)\n- `python-sdk/design.md` — SDK client implementation"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775877760866,"end":1775877760871}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775877760904,"sessionID":"ses_285712c33ffeKLPVuYWhDtZwf2","part":{"id":"prt_d7a90276a001aNot0LL7ak7jaX","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a8ee3f60015AAUDfF046ezaf","sessionID":"ses_285712c33ffeKLPVuYWhDtZwf2","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":34726,"input":16834,"output":2735,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15157}},"cost":0}}
